body:
--- "A {+(pack)-()|48} of wolves had to prepare themselves for winter. Their {+(litter)-()|48}
  of puppies were constantly hungry, but there was not much food around. The {+(flock)-()|48}
  of ducks by the lake had already flown south. There was a {+(swarm)-()|48} of flies
  buzzing around in its place. An {+(army)-()|48} of ants made their way back underground.\r\n\r\nThere
  once was a {+(team)-()|48} of oxen in a ranch off in the distance, but they had
  since disappeared. The lay of the land was empty, except for a {+(murder)-()|48}
  of crows passing by in the empty sky. The wolves knew they had to find a new home.\r\n"

--- "The daughter exclaimed, \"Father, please go ask the wall if he would be my husband.\"\r\n\r\nThe
  father then approached the wall and {+said,-said|164} \"Wall, will you be my {+daughter’s-daughters’|165}
  husband?\"\r\n\r\nThe wall was slow to reply. He finally answered and said, \"I
  am very strong, but the mouse is much stronger than me. He has {+dug-digged|227}
  many holes and tunnels underneath me, and there is nothing I can do to stop him.
  If your daughter wants the strongest possible husband, she should marry that mouse.\"\r\n"

--- "Holding the mouse gently in his hands, the man warmed the little creature with
  his {+breath.-breathe.|217} Much to the {+man’s-mans|165} amazement, the mouse then
  turned into a beautiful baby girl! The man thanked the {+gods-god’s|228} for their
  gift and rushed home to tell his wife what had happened. Joyfully, they {+raised-razed|218}
  the little girl as their own.\r\n\r\nWhen the girl had grown up, it was time to
  find her a husband. {+“What-What|164} kind of husband do you {+want?”-want|164}
  they asked her.\r\n\r\nThe daughter told them, \"I want to marry the {+strongest,-strongest|187}
  most powerful being in the world.\"\r\n\r\nHer mother thought about this for awhile
  and then said, \"I {+cannot-can not|221} think of anyone more powerful than the
  sun.\""
